## Proposed Changes

### 1. Backend: Dynamic Eligibility Engine

The hardcoded `if category in ["SC", "ST"] and income <= 250000` logic will be entirely removed.

#### [MODIFY] [main.py](file:///c:/Users/saich/samvaadAI/backend/main.py)
- Load the `scholarships.json` file on startup.
- Update the `/check-scholarship` route to iterate through all available scholarships in the JSON and check eligibility for each scheme individually.
- Return a list of *multiple* matched scholarships rather than a single true/false boolean.

#### [MODIFY] [explanation_agent.py](file:///c:/Users/saich/samvaadAI/backend/ai/explanation_agent.py)
- Update the logic so it dynamically generates explanations based on the specific `scholarships.json` rules that were matched or missed.

### 2. Backend: Persistent Agents

#### [MODIFY] [logger_agent.py](file:///c:/Users/saich/samvaadAI/backend/ai/logger_agent.py)
- Currently, logs are stored in memory and lost when the server restarts. I will modify the agent to persistently write to local JSON files (e.g., `fraud_logs.json` and `analytics.json`).

### 3. Frontend: Premium Redesign

The current MVP UI will be replaced with a stunning, national-grade interface.

#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/saich/samvaadAI/frontend/index.html) & [style.css](file:///c:/Users/saich/samvaadAI/frontend/style.css)
- Implement a deep, modern aesthetic featuring glassmorphic cards, gradient text, and dynamic hover states.
- The UI will be rebuilt to display a grid of eligible scholarships rather than a simple text output.

#### [MODIFY] [app.js](file:///c:/Users/saich/samvaadAI/frontend/app.js)
- Update the payload parser to handle the new backend response format (arrays of eligible scholarships) and dynamically render HTML cards for each match.

### 4. Frontend: The Admin Dashboard

#### [MODIFY] [admin.html](file:///c:/Users/saich/samvaadAI/frontend/admin.html)
- Currently, `admin.html` exists but we need to ensure it communicates with the existing `/admin/logs` routes.
- I will build a secure-looking, dark-mode analytics dashboard that visualizes system traffic and flagged fraud attempts.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- No automated tests are currently present, but I will manually test the backend using curl commands or Python scripts to ensure `scholarships.json` is accurately filtering users.

### Manual Verification
- You will need to spin up the FastAPI server (`uvicorn backend.main:app --reload`) and open `index.html` in your browser.
- Verify that different combinations of category and income accurately return the respective scholarships listed in the JSON file.
